text:
In light of winter weather, here are some tips from @indygobus:
1. Wear warm, highly visible clothing so you can be spotted at a bus stop.
2. Allow for extra travel time to and from your destination. Plan for delays due to icy streets, heavy snowfall, and traffic congestion.

I can feel that! I do see it just causing problems that won’t be worth the payoff. I’ve worked downtown on the streets for 12 years and some of these adjustments are honestly head scratching.

text_html: I can feel that! I do see it just causing problems that won’t be worth the payoff. I’ve worked downtown on the streets for 12 years and some of these adjustments are honestly head scratching. Mainly, taking Capital from 4 to 2 lanes & no right turns on Meridian.

Indy public transit is so far behind.
